@(30-36=c536.I.30) @wDN{Enlil} joyfully addressed @wGN{Sumer}. In a …… of abundance he raised …… to the duties of shepherd. In order to build the …… of @wDN{Enlil}, to bring forth the houses of the great gods, to raise the banks of the levees and ditches, @wDN{Enlil} gave strength to the shepherd @wRN{Ur-@wDN{Namma}} in his majestic arms.

@(37-44=c536.I.37) On @wRN{Ur-@wDN{Namma}} receiving …… and kingship, after he …… a good ……, Strong Copper helped him mightily. With it, the shepherd @wRN{Ur-@wDN{Namma}} …… in great amounts. With it, he …… the great temple of @wDN{Suen} in @wSN{Urim}. With it, he …… the @wTN{E-kur}, the house of @wDN{Enlil} in @wSN{Nibru}. He made famous the houses of the great gods, and raised high the banks of the levees and ditches.

@(45-58=c536.I.45) Under him, his city ……. Under him, wool ……. Under him, oil ……. Under him, the people eat excellent food. @wRN{Ur-@wDN{Namma}} …… broad wisdom. Strong Copper …… great ……. When raising ……, he ……. He called the one giving …… as his …… singer. The …… of bright ……. He investigated the …… of Strong Copper. …… their helpers. In order to build his ……. Not neglecting …….
